scaffold widget =>> is the widget responisble for applying MAterialApp instructios
it implements the guidlines of MaterialApp,   so without scaffold, there will be no effect for MaterialApp
the application contain more than one screen,   and scaffold create screen
so if u have 3 scaffold then u hae 3 screens ... and so on

void main(){
  runApp(
    MaterialApp(
      home: Scaffold(
        floatingActionButton: FloatingActionButton( onPressed: (){}, ),
        appBar: AppBar(
            title: Text("NearBY_U")
        ),
        body: Center(
            child: Text('Hello World'),
        ),
      ),
    ),
  );
}

scaffold  =>> create new screen
            - split the screen into 3 parts (AppBar, body, floatingActionButton)
            - implements the instructions of MaterialApp,  without it , nothing will be changed
            - each scaffold  = one screen
